modules.description: Provides functions to translate strings at runtime and extract translatable content during compilation, using localized message catalogs. Works with strings and format strings, supporting pluralization and formatted output. Enables display of user-specific language messages, such as showing "bonjour" for French speakers and "hello" for English speakers.

Provides access to the native gettext library for internationalization, enabling translation of strings at runtime. Exposes functions for loading message catalogs and retrieving localized strings. Supports handling of domain-specific translations and character encoding conversions. Can be used to dynamically switch languages or fetch translated error messages in applications.

Provides functions to manage locale settings, look up translated strings, and handle plural forms using the gettext C library. Works with locale categories, message domains, and character encodings to customize translation behavior. Enables dynamic translation of application messages based on user locale and domain-specific catalogs.
